name: ORIGINAL LINOPRINT - 'NUT ROCK TO ST. MARY'S QUAY'
description:
Limited edition print by Reverend Troutbeck, inspired by the magic of the Scilly Isles Gig Rowing Championships. Hand-cut and printed on a 1904 proofing press in the West Country.

The image is printed in blue grey ink on off-white, archival printmaking paper. Each edition will be titled, signed and numbered, and only 50 editions will be produced. Mounting and framing is not included. Dimensions 49cm by 34.5cm.

A special and affordable original artwork for any gig rowing enthusiast.
